    "# Prior-Driven Drift Diagnostics\n",
    "\n",
    "Verify that the score-based drift (`x ← x + ε · score(x)`) is working\n",
    "correctly by checking three expected signatures:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Raw score norm decreases** — points approach the mode where ∇ log p is small.\n",
    "2. **Distance to nearest clean encoding decreases** — drift pulls noisy points back.\n",
    "3. **Log-likelihood increases** — histogram of Δlog p shifts rightward over time.\n",
    "\n",
    "Uses `utls.drift_diagnostics` which tracks cumulative Δlog p via the\n",
    "first-order Taylor expansion: Δlog p ≈ score(x) · Δx."
   ]
